CatDescriptText: Cutline of image and article published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1969, pg.1. reads: "PICKETING AT SEARS - These youthful members of one of the NAACP Youth Units are shown picketing at Sears East Liberty store Monday night. Picketing began to be expanded this week with almost daily demonstrations.  Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Three young women and young man from NAACP Youth Unit protesting outside of Sears department store, with signs reading "Down with Tokenism" and "Equal Job Opportunities for All"
